title: A7
description: What is the tissue specificity of the EGFR protein?

cypher_result: Ubiquitously expressed. Isoform 2 is also expressed in ovarian cancers.

Ubiquitously expressed in embryos. In larvae, uniform expression is seen in wing disks, genital disk, anlagen of testis and ovary, and brain cortex. In eye-antenna disk, highest expression is anterior to morphogenetic furrow, levels remain high in photoreceptor precursor cells. This pattern is reversed in posterior eye disk. In adults expression is high in brain cortex and thoracic and abdominal ganglia.

title: C3
description: Which cancer samples have under expression of AKT3 protein? Show sample name, regulation, and cancer type.

version_1.cypher_query: MATCH (p:Protein {hasPrimaryName: 'AKT3'})-[r:HASPROTEIN]->(ge:GeneExpression {hasRegulation: 'under'}) MATCH (ge)-[:INSAMPLE]->(s:Sample) MATCH (s)-[:IMPLICATEDIN]->(c:Cancer) RETURN s.hasSampleName AS SampleName, ge.hasRegulation AS Regulation, c.hasPrimaryName AS CancerType LIMIT 100

title: C4
description: Which sequence motifs are hallmarks for the Human_EGFR family?

version_1.cypher_query: MATCH (f:Family {hasPrimaryName: 'Human_EGFR'})-[:ENCODEDIN]->(p:Protein) MATCH (p)-[:HASSEQUENCE]->(s:Sequence) MATCH (s)-[:HASMOTIF]->(m:SequenceMotif) RETURN m.hasPrimaryName LIMIT 100

title: C5
description: What are the histology subtypes of cancers linked to samples that have proteins with mutation ID 'COSM4166151'?

version_1.cypher_query: MATCH (p:Protein)-[:HASMUTATION]->(m:Missense {hasMutationId: 'COSM4166151'}) MATCH (p)<-[:HASPROTEIN]-(g:GeneExpression)-[:INSAMPLE]->(s:Sample) MATCH (s)-[:IMPLICATEDIN]->(c:Cancer) RETURN DISTINCT c.hasHistologySubType LIMIT 100

title: C6
description: What is the name of the organism for proteins belonging to the Plant clade?

version_1.cypher_query: MATCH (clade:CladeCladeTaxonomicgroupscategorizingorganismsbasedonsharedcharacteristics {hasPrimaryName: 'Plant'}) MATCH (organism:Organism)-[:ISPARTOF]->(clade) MATCH (protein:Protein)-[:PRESENTIN]->(organism) RETURN organism.hasPrimaryName LIMIT 100

title: C7
description: Find pathways that include proteins containing the functional domain 'PI3_PI4_kinase' and have mutations. Please provide the names of these pathways and descriptions of the mutations.

version_1.cypher_query: MATCH (fd:FunctionalDomain {hasPrimaryName: 'PI3_PI4_kinase'})<-[:HASFUNCTIONALDOMAIN]-(p:Protein) MATCH (p)-[:HASMUTATION]->(m) MATCH (p)-[:PARTICIPATESIN]->(path:Pathway) RETURN DISTINCT path.hasPrimaryName AS pathwayName,         CASE             WHEN m:Missense THEN m.hasMutationDescription             ELSE m.hasMutationDescription         END AS mutationDescription LIMIT 100
